<br>
the caller will lead you to a spot an summon mobs to fight.<br>
<br>
At the easiest level spawns come every 3 minutes. between 2 and 3.<br>
 <br>
They arent hard at all, but a chanter to mez is a must. Mages work great in these groups too, cuz you never know when you will need mod rods in a fix.<br>
<br>
Occassionally named pop, they drop cool stuff, like a the new Fungi and other stuffs.<br>
<br>
But the best part is, You never have to pull, and the exp is nice, and constant, you never have to worry about running out of spawns.<br>
<br>
You can end it at anytime by handing in a note, good idea if you start falling behind on the spawns.<br>
<br>
Also a rogue is a good idea, killing these quick is key. Cleric, and melee to fill out your group and kill away. <p><img src=http://photos.netclubs.com/live/photos/photocenter/9/a/g/e/ge31rtf4brah3bpd0188nc11hc/sig.JPG></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usehra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sehra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 399<br> <font color=#333333>(2/20/02 3:35:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=122.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Callers, not a solo camp</span><hr size=1> I killed the callers ONCE while in an AoE group without realizing it, and took sufficient faction hits to move down to dubious. Now I can't do the quest handin myself <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
